election_record.label: New Jersey 1818 U.S. House of Representatives

overview.note: The newspapers reported that there was a considerable amount of scattered votes, however they only listed the returns for the following persons: Lewis Condit, John Frelinghuysen, James Parker, Jesse Upson, Benjamin Bennet.

sub_unit.name: Cape May
sub_unit.note: The True American November 2, 1818, The Centinel of Freedom (Newark, NJ) November 3, 1818 and The Fredonian (New Brunswick, NJ) November 3, 1818, list 45 votes for Joseph Bloomfield in Cape May County.

sub_unit.name: Essex
sub_unit.note: The Palladium of Liberty October 22, 1818, New-Jersey Journal (Elizabethtown, NJ) October 20, 1818, The Centinel of Freedom (Newark, NJ) October 20, 1818, The Whig October 26, 1818 and the Palladium of Liberty October 22, 1818 list 1324 votes for Joseph Bloomfield.

sub_unit.name: Middlesex
sub_unit.note: The True American November 2, 1818, The Centinel of Freedom (Newark, NJ), The Fredonian (New Brunswick, NJ) November 3, 1818 and the Centinel of Freedom November 3, 1818 list 573 votes for Charles Kinsey.

sub_unit.name: Morris
sub_unit.note: The Palladium of Liberty October 22 1818 and the Centinel of Freedom October 27, 1818 list 1560 votes for Bernard Smith, 1395 votes for Henry Southard and 460 votes for John Condict.

sub_unit.name: Somerset
sub_unit.note: The True American November 2, 1818 list 91 votes for Charles Kinsey.

sub_unit.name: Byram
sub_unit.note: Charles Kinsey received 67 votes with the wrong county listed.

sub_unit.name: Hardiston
sub_unit.note: Charles Kinsey received 249 votes with the wrong county listed.

sub_unit.name: Vernon
sub_unit.note: Charles Kinsey received 175 votes with the wrong county listed.

sub_unit.name: Wantage
sub_unit.note: Charles Kinsey received 188 votes with the wrong county listed.
